4/janelle-monae-pynk-video-tessa-thompson-dirty-computer|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|location=New York City|accessdate=June 20, 2018|date=April 10, 2018}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"Moonlight\"\n| [[Jay-Z]]\n| [[Monica Geller]]\n|<center><ref>{{cite web|last=Framke|first=Caroline|title=The video for Jay-Z's \"Moonlight\" is an all-black Friends remake \u2014 until it's not\n|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2017/8/4/16100084/watch-jay-z-moonlight-video-youtube-tidal-black-friends|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|location=New York City|accessdate=June 20, 2018|date=August 4, 2017}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2018\n| \"[[Make Me Feel (Janelle Mon\u00e1e song)|Make Me Feel]]\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Janelle Mon\u00e1e\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Zen / Mary Apple 53\n|rowspan=\"3\"|<center><ref>{{cite web|last=Grierson|first=Tim|title=Why Janelle Monae's 'Dirty Computer' Film Is a Timely New Sci-Fi Masterpiece|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/janelle-monae-dirty-computer-film-sci-fi-masterpiece-w519519|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=Wenner Media LLC|location=New York City|accessdate=April 27, 2018|date=April 27, 2018}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| \"[[Pynk]]\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| \"Screwed\"\n|-\n| \"[[Uneventful Days]]\"\n| [[Beck]]\n| Herself\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Work\n! Result\n! {{abbr|Ref.|reference}}\n|-\n|2009\n|[[American Black Film Festival]]\n|Best Actor\n|''Mississippi Damned''\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=2009 Winners |url=http://www.abff.com/archives/history-of-winners/2009-winners/ |publisher=American Black Film Festival |accessdate=June 18, 2016 |archivedate=February 7, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207152429/http://www.abff.com/archives/history-of-winners/2009-winners/ |url-status = live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2011\n|[[Black Reel Awards of 2011|Black Reel Awards]]\n|[[Black Reel Award for Best Breakthrough Performance|Best Breakthrough Performance]]\n|''For Colored Girls''\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Winners > 2011 |publisher=Black Reel Awards |url=https://blackreelawards.wordpress.com/winners/ |accessdate=June 18, 2016 |archivedate=January 14, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160114134431/https://blackreelawards.wordpress.com/winners/ |url-status = live|date=February 12, 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2014\n|[[Gotham Independent Film Awards 2014|Gotham Awards]]\n|[[Gotham Independent Film Award for Breakthrough Actor|Breakthrough Actor]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|''Dear White People''\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 Gotham Awards: Complete Winners List |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/2014-gotham-awards-complete-winners-753012 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 18, 2016 |archivedate=December 27, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227164332/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/2014-gotham-awards-complete-winners-753012 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[African-American Film Critics Association Awards 2014|African-American Film Critics Association]]\n|Breakthrough Performance\n|{{won}}\n|<ref name=\"imdbawards\">{{cite web|title=Tessa Thompson \u2013 Awards \u2013 IMDb|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1935086/awards?ref_=nm_awd|accessdate=July 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2015\n|[[46th NAACP Image Awards|NAACP Image Awards]]\n|[[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Actress in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Actress in a Motion Picture]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-naacp-image-awards-2014-full-list-of-nominees-20141209-story.html |title=NAACP Image Awards 2015: Full list of nominees and winners |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=February 6, 2015 |archivedate=December 23, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223231659/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-naacp-image-awards-2014-full-list-of